CVector, FieldVector
public abstract class DenseFieldVectorBase<T extends DenseFieldVectorBase<T,U,V,W>,U extends DenseFieldMatrixBase<U,?,?,T,W>,V extends CooFieldVectorBase<V,?,T,U,W>,W extends Field<W>> extends FieldTensorBase<T,T,W> implements DenseVectorMixin<T,V,U,Field<W>[],W>

A dense vector whose entries are field elements.

Vectors are 1D tensors (i.e. rank 1 tensor).

Field vectors have mutable entries but a fixed size.

    • stack

      public U stack(T b, int axis)

      Stacks two vectors along specified axis.

      Stacking two vectors of length n along axis 0 stacks the vectors as if they were row vectors resulting in a 2-by-n matrix.

      Stacking two vectors of length n along axis 1 stacks the vectors as if they were column vectors resulting in a n-by-2 matrix.

      Specified by:
      stack in interface VectorMatrixOpsMixin<T extends DenseFieldVectorBase<T,U,V,W>,U extends DenseFieldMatrixBase<U,?,?,T,W>,V extends CooFieldVectorBase<V,?,T,U,W>>
      Parameters:
      b - VectorOld to stack with this vector.
      axis - Axis along which to stack vectors. If axis=0, then vectors are stacked as if they are row vectors. If axis=1, then vectors are stacked as if they are column vectors.
      Returns:
      The result of stacking this vector and the vector b.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the number of entries in this vector is different from the number of entries in the vector b.
      IllegalArgumentException - If axis is not either 0 or 1.

      public boolean allClose(T b, double relTol, double absTol)
      Checks if all entries of this vector are close to the entries of b.
      Specified by:
      allClose in interface DenseTensorMixin<T extends DenseFieldVectorBase<T,U,V,W>,U extends DenseFieldMatrixBase<U,?,?,T,W>>
      Parameters:
      b - Vector to compare this tensor to.
      relTol - Relative tolerance.
      absTol - Absolute tolerance.
      Returns:
      True if b is the same shape as this tensor and all entries are 'close', i.e. elements x and y at the same positions in the two vectors respectively satisfy |x-y| <= (atol + rtol*|y|). Otherwise, returns false.
      See Also:
      • DenseTensorMixin.allClose(DenseTensorMixin)
